comment: The Knaster-Tarski theorem says that every monotone function over a complete lattice has a (least) fixpoint. Here we specialize this theorem to the case when the lattice is the powerset lattice ` ~P A ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 11-Jun-2015.)
